description:
AutoCellCapEstFunction: Table storing automatic cell capacity estimation function parameters for specific cells, including timestamps, location, cell identifiers, data type, version, and function usage flags.
- dateTime: Timestamp of the record.
- Area_Name: Name of the geographical area where the cell is located.
- CellId: Unique identifier for the cell.
- Id2: Redundant identifier for the cell (appears to be identical to CellId).
- Id3:  An additional, currently unused identifier (sample value is '1').
- vsDataType: Data type identifier.
- vsDataFormatVersion: Version of the data format.
- AutoCellCapEstFunction.autoCellCapEstFunctionId: Unique ID for the specific auto cell capacity estimation function instance.
- AutoCellCapEstFunction.useEstimatedCellCap: Boolean flag indicating whether the estimated cell capacity is used.
